1. DEFINITIONS

"Estate Kit" refers to the proprietary software platform, including all physical and digital components, developed and owned by Estate Kit Inc.

"Software" means the complete Estate Kit solution, including but not limited to source code, documentation, assets, configurations, physical kit components, digital vault infrastructure, security protocols, and business workflows.

"Licensee" refers to the authorized user or entity granted access to use Estate Kit services.

"Confidential Information" includes all proprietary information, technical data, trade secrets, and know-how related to Estate Kit.

2. GRANT OF LICENSE

Estate Kit Inc. grants Licensee a limited, non-transferable, non-exclusive right to use the Software solely for authorized estate planning purposes in accordance with the subscription terms and conditions.

3. RESTRICTIONS

Licensee shall not:
a) Redistribute, modify, sublicense, or transfer the Software
b) Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software
c) Use the Software for competitive purposes
d) Attempt to circumvent security measures
e) Access the system without authorization
f) Create derivative works based on the Software
g) Remove or alter any proprietary notices

4. PROPRIETARY RIGHTS

Estate Kit Inc. retains all right, title, and interest in:
a) Frontend application code
b) Backend services code
c) Infrastructure configurations
d) Database schemas
e) API specifications
f) User interface designs
g) Business logic
h) Integration implementations
i) Security architecture
j) Data encryption protocols
k) Access control mechanisms
l) Document management systems
m) Delegate access frameworks
n) Physical kit designs
o) Digital vault architecture

5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The Software integrates with third-party services subject to their respective terms:
a) Auth0 - Authentication and identity management (OAuth 2.0/OIDC standards)
b) Shopify - E-commerce platform integration (PCI DSS standards)
c) SendGrid - Communication services (CASL requirements)
d) Intercom - Customer support integration (Data privacy standards)
e) Sanity.io - Content management (Content security standards)
f) AWS services - Cloud infrastructure (SOC 2 standards)

